      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 1988: loadMissingBodyOverwrites() calls transformSwarmMessages() synchronously from the loadMessages callback path. Plugin transforms can be expensive or plugin-controlled, so this can block delivery of SwarmLoaded follow-up processing and potentially stall the conversation thread/UI-facing signal flow for large histories. Consider dispatching the transform work asynchronously, similar to other plugin work, and only taking loadedHistory_.mutex for snapshot/writeback.\n```suggestion\n// Queue plugin transform work off the load callback thread, then emit updates when complete.\ndht::ThreadPool::io().run([w \u003d weak_from_this()] {\n    if (auto self \u003d w.lock())\n        self-\u003eloadMissingBodyOverwrites();\n});\n```",
