      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 2004: The batch includes every loaded TEXT message missing bodyOverwrite, including local messages. Earlier publishMessage() is constructed with the incoming/outgoing flag, but transformSwarmMessages() receives only SwarmMessage and cannot distinguish direction unless it infers from author. If body overwrites are intended only for remote messages, this may unexpectedly translate/replace the user\u0027s own messages. Filter on author before adding to the batch or document that plugins must handle both directions.\n```suggestion\nif (msg-\u003etype \u003d\u003d CommitType::TEXT\n    \u0026\u0026 msg-\u003ebody.at(CommitKey::AUTHOR) !\u003d userId_\n    \u0026\u0026 !msg-\u003epluginData.contains(\"bodyOverwrite\")) {\n    batch.push_back(*msg);\n}\n```",
